I believe our current process is not working effectively, particularly with the SonarQube quality gate.

On feature branches, the Sonar gate consistently passes during builds. However, once the code is merged into the Develop branch, we start seeing coverage issues. By that time, the code has already been deployed to the environment and QA testing has been completed.

If QA approves the changes and we then merge into Develop, only at that point do we discover the actual Sonar issues. This results in rework—fixing the issues and requesting QA to retest—which leads to duplicated effort and inefficiency.

It would be better to identify and enforce Sonar coverage requirements earlier in the process (e.g., at the feature branch or PR level) so that issues are caught before QA testing and deployment.